Dear <%= @application_form.first_name %>,

# Application decision

<% if @application_form.rejected_by_default %>
  Your application for <%= @course.name_and_code %> has been automatically rejected because <%= @course.provider.name %> did not respond in time.
<% else %>
  <%= @course.provider.name %> has decided not to progress your teacher training application for <%= @course.name_and_code %> on this occasion.
<% end %>

# You may still be able to get a place on a course

Your <%= @application_form.application_choices.count > 1 ? 'provider has' : 'providers have' %> left you some feedback. There may be things you can do to get a place on a course this year, next year or in the future.

<% unless @application_form.rejected_by_default %>
  Review your feedback:

  <%= @candidate_magic_link %>
<% end %>

# Applying again this year

If now’s the right time for you, it’s easy to apply again this year. We’ve saved your last application, so all you have to do is sign in, choose a course, make any changes and submit.

Sign in to apply again:

<%= @candidate_magic_link %>

# Get help

We’re here to help you get a place on a course. Call Get Into Teaching for free on 0800 389 2500 or chat to an adviser online:

https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk/contacts

For any technical issues using Apply for teacher training, contact us at [becomingateacher@digital.education.gov.uk](mailto:becomingateacher@digital.education.gov.uk)
